<p><strong>World History Guided Reading Activity 8.1 Answer Key PDF: Unraveling the Ancient World</strong></p>
<p><strong>Paragraph 1: Mesopotamia</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Question:</strong> What is the name of the first civilization to develop writing?</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> Mesopotamia</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Question:</strong> What were some of the major accomplishments of the Mesopotamian civilization?</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> Invention of writing, wheeled vehicles, irrigation systems, and complex social structures</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Paragraph 2: Egypt</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Question:</strong> What was the name of the Egyptian writing system that combined hieroglyphics, hieratic, and demotic scripts?</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> Medu Neter</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Question:</strong> What was the purpose of the pyramids in Egypt?</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> Tombs for pharaohs and symbols of their power</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Paragraph 3: Indus Valley Civilization</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Question:</strong> What were some of the urban planning features of the Indus Valley Civilization?</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> Grid-like city planning, running water, and indoor plumbing</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Question:</strong> Why did the Indus Valley Civilization decline?</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> Reasons are still unknown, but theories include climate change and invasions</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Paragraph 4: China</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Question:</strong> Who is considered the first emperor of unified China?</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> Qin Shi Huang</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Question:</strong> What was the purpose of the Great Wall of China?</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> To protect the empire from nomadic invasions</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Paragraph 5: Greece and Rome</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Question:</strong> What is the name of the Greek philosophy that emphasized rational thinking and logic?</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> Socratic method</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Question:</strong> What was the significance of the Roman Empire?</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> Largest empire in Western history, spread Roman law, infrastructure, and culture across Europe and North Africa</p>
</li>
</ul>